Former American football star OJ Simpson was questioned by Las Vegas police over an alleged armed robbery at a casino hotel room.
Simpson, released without charge, was assisting the investigation.
The incident involved Simpson and a group of men entering a room under false pretenses.
He was previously found liable in a civil suit related to a 1997 case.
Simpson, facing multiple charges, denied involvement in the robbery.
Witnesses stated Simpson did not possess a gun during the incident.
The ongoing investigation includes the arrest of another man, Walter Alexander, in connection with the alleged robbery of sports memorabilia.
